  <h1>
   xboxlive_user_id_for_user
  </h1>
  This function converts the User ID pointer into a string.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">xboxlive_user_id_for_user(user_id);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      user_id
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/UWP_And_XBox_Live/Users_And_Accounts/xboxlive_get_user.htm">
        Xbox User ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The ID pointer of the user to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 String
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var _uid = xboxlive_user_for_pad(0); uid_string = xboxlive_user_id_for_user(_uid);
</code></pre>
  The above code gets the user ID pointer for the user assigned to the gamepad [0] slot, and then saves that user ID as a string to an instance variable.
